SIMPLE: counterfoil
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Counterfoil
<hw>Coun"ter*foil`</hw> <pr>(-foil)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Counter-</ets> + <ets>foil</ets> a leaf.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>That part of a tally, formerly in the exchequer,
which was kept by an officer in that court, the other, called the
<xex>stock</xex>, being delivered to the person who had lent the king
money on the account; -- called also
<altname>counterstock</altname>.</def> <mark>[Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The part of a writing (as the stub of a bank check)
in which are noted the main particulars contained in the corresponding
part, which has been issued.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Counterforce</ent>⟦br⟧
